rComments: Her quizzes and final were so difficult. Class average for our transcription quiz was in the 50s. She tested on stuff she skims through or did not even mention in class. Her lectures are very dry.
She doesn't provide answers to any assignments, any test, and any tutorial questions. You don't have the time to ask it during tutorial neither.

Lectures were dry and she seemed awkward at the podium but she was a really sweet professor. Her homework assignments and tests were fair (and she allowed a cheat sheet!). The only reason you need the textbook is to do weekly reading response questions, otherwise don't waste your time--everything you need is in lecture.
